Sometime in mid-May, 1946, I traveled to New York--a five-hour traintrip--to lunch with a publisher who was offering me better terms for acollection of stories (Exile from Mayda) than good Lodge. After a pleasantmeal, in the sunny haze of that banal day, I walked over to the <136> PublicLibrary, and by a banal miracle of synchronization she came dancing downthose very steps, Dolly von Borg, now twenty-four, as I trudged up towardher, a fat famo